**Blurr Bureau Reimagines Yes! Apples as a Modern Consumer Brand**  

New York branding studio Blurr Bureau has launched a vibrant rebrand for Yes! Apples, a collective of small family-run orchards in the state. The project aimed to transform apples—long marketed as a commodity—into a modern consumer brand, addressing a key challenge: shoppers often stick to familiar varieties due to lack of information.  

The identity blends nostalgia (fruit stickers, market signs) with bold, shelf-catching design to stand out in the "sleepy" produce aisle. Standout elements include:  
- Color-coded packaging for different apple varieties;  
- Fun stickers with nutrition/flavor details to encourage trying new types;  
- A logo nodding to Milton Glaser’s "I Love NY" (apple at its core) and a hidden tree/seed illustration in the "Y" of "Yes!";  
- Typography pairing Displaay’s Perfekta (soft, apple-shaped letterforms) with Exposure (2025TF) for modern-nostalgic balance.  

State pride is woven throughout ("Yes! We’re grown in NYC" on every sticker), while the design evokes joy and freshness—repositioning a culturally embedded food as something new and characterful.
